HEADWORD: Autocrat
<hw>Au"to*crat</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/
self + <?/ strength, <?/ strong: cf. F. <ets>autocrate</ets>. See
<er>Hard</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An absolute
sovereign; a monarch who holds and exercises the powers of government by
claim of absolute right, not subject to restriction; <as>as,
<ex>Autocrat</ex> of all the Russias (a title of the
Czar)</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who rules with undisputed sway in any company or
relation; a despot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>autocrat</qex> of the breakfast table.</q>
<rj><qau>Holmes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Autocratical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Autocratic</ent>⟦br⟧
